==English==
===Noun===
'''ark''' (plural: '''arks''')
# (archaic or specialized:) something affording protection or safety.
# spacious boat.
# (Judaism:) consecrated container.

==== Etymology ====
From the [[Latin]] "''arca''"  meaning "[[chest]]" (container).

====Translations====
'''boat'''
*French: [[arche]] {{f}}
'''consecrated container'''
*French: [[arche]] {{f}}

